The above file has a total size footprint of ~ 35 KB, this makes it within the realm of viability to store entirely on Ethereum L1 (it costs roughly ~ 0.015 ETH per KB to write project code to Ethereum, assuming a gas price of 20 gwei).

We understand that there may be cases where artists wish to use large libraries, e.g. p5.js - this library has a footprint of 6.19 MB, which would cost around 92.85 ETH to write to Ethereum storage (~ $150k). Therefore, we recommend following this guideline when third-party libraries are used within a project:

Import/load third-party libraries in a way that is appropriate to your project (e.g. via <script> tags in the case of client-side Javascript).

This enables Tonic to write an artist's own code to Ethereum, without including third-party library code in the on-chain bundle.
